  "output": "Confirmed all five findings against source. Here's the report.\n\n## 1. N+1 Query Patterns\n\n**`VoucherService.loadAccounts`** — `Avelo/Core/Services/VoucherService.swift:1164-1175`\n```swift\nprivate func loadAccounts(ids: Set<Account.ID>, accountRepo: AccountRepository) throws -> [Account.ID: Account] {\n    var out: [Account.ID: Account] = [:]\n    for id in ids {\n        guard let account = try accountRepo.findById(id) else { throw AppError.notFound(\"Account\") }\n        out[id] = account\n    }\n    return out\n}\n```\nRuns once per distinct account, once per draft, inside `postBatch`'s loop — one `SELECT` per account per voucher on bulk import. `AccountRepository` already has the batch version one file over (`findByCodes`, line 63). Add the ID equivalent and call it once:\n```swift\n// AccountRepository.swift\npublic func findByIds(_ ids: [Account.ID], companyId: Company.ID) throws -> [Account.ID: Account] {\n    guard !ids.isEmpty else { return [:] }\n    let placeholders = Array(repeating: \"?\", count: ids.count).joined(separator: \",\")\n    var out: [Account.ID: Account] = [:]\n    _ = try db.query(\"SELECT \\(Self.selectColumns) FROM avelo_accounts WHERE company_id = ? AND id IN (\\(placeholders))\",\n                      bind: [.text(companyId.uuidString)] + ids.map { .text($0.uuidString) }) { row in\n        let a = try Self.rowToAccount(row); out[a.id] = a\n    }\n    return out\n}\n\n// VoucherService.swift\nprivate func loadAccounts(ids: Set<Account.ID>, accountRepo: AccountRepository) throws -> [Account.ID: Account] {\n    let found = try accountRepo.findByIds(Array(ids), companyId: companyId)\n    guard found.count == ids.count else { throw AppError.notFound(\"Account\") }\n    return found\n}\n```\nThis exact pattern was already flagged in an earlier session (Jul 9) and not yet fixed — worth prioritizing since it's on the hot posting path.\n\n**`stockValuation`** — `Avelo/Core/Repositories/ReportRepository+ComplianceReports.swift:195-229`\n```swift\nlet rows = try items.map { item in\n    let totals = try inventory.runningBalance(itemId: item.id, asOf: asOfDate)  // 2 queries per item\n    ...\n}\n```\n`stockAgeing`, the next function in the *same file* (line 232), does this correctly with one `IN (...)` query for all items. Mirror that instead of calling `runningBalance` per item.\n\n**`AccountTreeCache.reload`** — `Avelo/Core/Cache/AccountTreeCache.swift:58-67` — falls back to a fresh `movementTotals` query per ledger whenever no FY-carried opening balance row exists, inside `ledgers.map`. Batch the fallback the same way `loadLedgerBalances` right below it already does.\n\n**`DashboardViewModel.reload`** — `Avelo/Features/Dashboard/DashboardViewModel.swift:84-104` — loops month-by-month calling `profitAndLoss` (≈8-10 joined queries each) just to pull one number per month → 100+ queries per dashboard load. Replace with one `GROUP BY strftime('%Y-%m', v.date)` query.\n\n**`BOMService.validateBOMInput`** — `Avelo/Core/Services/BOMService.swift:75-87` — same per-item lookup pattern as above, fixable the same way.\n\n## 2. SwiftUI Unnecessary Recomputation\n\n**`VouchersViewModel.accountName`** — `Avelo/Features/Vouchers/VouchersViewModel.swift:108-110`\n```swift\npublic func accountName(_ id: Account.ID) -> String {\n    accounts.first(where: { $0.id == id })?.name ?? id.uuidString.prefix(8) + \"…\"\n}\n```\nCalled per visible table row on every render/scroll → O(rows × accounts), even though `accounts` only changes on `reload()`. Cache a dictionary alongside it:\n```swift\nprivate var accountsById: [Account.ID: Account] = [:]\n// set accountsById = Dictionary(uniqueKeysWithValues: accounts.map { ($0.id, $0) }) wherever `accounts` is assigned in reload()\n\npublic func accountName(_ id: Account.ID) -> String {\n    accountsById[id]?.name ?? id.uuidString.prefix(8) + \"…\"\n}\n```\n\n**`DashboardViewModel.reload`** doesn't hop off `@MainActor` — every sibling ViewModel (`VouchersViewModel`, `AccountsViewModel`, `InventoryViewModel`...) wraps reload in `Task.detached`, this one doesn't (`DashboardViewModel.swift:31`). Combined with the N+1 monthly loop above, it blocks the main thread/UI while running.\n\n**`VoucherEditViewModel.isBalanced`** — `Avelo/Features/Vouchers/VoucherEditViewModel.swift:348-367` recomputes two full-array passes with string reparsing (`Currency.parseRupeeInput`) on every access, feeding `canPost`. See fix in §5 — same root cause as the redundant-computation finding.\n\n## 3. Caching Opportunities\n\n**`ReportService`** — `Avelo/Core/Services/ReportService.swift:81-109` has a working `ReportCache` used by `ledger`/`trialBalance`/`profitAndLoss`/`balanceSheet` (lines 31-79), but `gstSummary`, `dayBook`, `outstanding`, `stockValuation`, `cashFlow`, `stockAgeing` skip it entirely:\n```swift\npublic func gstSummary(fromDate: Date, toDate: Date) throws -> ReportResult.GstSummary {\n    let f = makeFilter()\n    return try repository.gstSummary(fromDate: fromDate, toDate: toDate, filter: f)   // no cache\n}\n```\nWrap these the same way `profitAndLoss` does (build a `ReportCache.Key`, check, compute, store) — `gstSummary` and `stockValuation` are the two most expensive calls in the file and both are hit on every Dashboard/GST view load.\n\nNote from memory: an earlier session already flagged that `changeToken` verification runs on *every* cached-report access — worth checking whether that itself is cheap enough to not offset the win here.\n\n**`DashboardViewModel.reload`** re-fetches accounts and does linear lookups instead of using the app-level `AccountTreeCache` at `AppEnvironment.swift:13,268-269` that's already reloaded on company/FY open.\n\n## 4. Memory Leaks\n\nCodebase is disciplined: no raw `Timer`/`NotificationCenter.addObserver`, `[weak self]` used consistently in every `Task.detached`. One real finding:\n\n**Company switch leaks the previous SQLite connection** — `Avelo/Core/Database/DatabaseManager.swift:156-192` + `Avelo/Features/Onboarding/OpenCompanySheet.swift:36-42`. `OpenCompanySheet` calls `env.openCompany(entry.id)` directly without calling `env.closeCompany()` on the currently-open company first, so `DatabaseManager.openHandles` accumulates one open `SQLiteDatabase`/WAL connection per switch, for the app's lifetime.\n```swift\n// OpenCompanySheet, before opening the new one:\nif let current = env.companyContext?.id, current != entry.id {\n    env.closeCompany(current)\n}\nTask { await env.openCompany(entry.id); router.presentedSheet = nil }\n```\n\n## 5. Redundant Computations\n\n**`VoucherDraft.totalDebitPaise`/`totalCreditPaise`** — `Avelo/Core/Models/VoucherDraft.swift:78-99` each call `checkedTotals()`, which computes *both* sums, then discards the one it didn't ask for:\n```swift\npublic var totalDebitPaise: Int64 { (try? checkedTotals().debit) ?? 0 }\npublic var totalCreditPaise: Int64 { (try? checkedTotals().credit) ?? 0 }\n```\n`VoucherService.postWithoutCacheInvalidation` reads both independently at lines 178, 214, 346 — three full passes over `lines` per post, each doing double the necessary work. Cache the tuple once per post instead of calling the properties repeatedly:\n```swift\nlet totals = try normalizedDraft.checkedTotals()  // compute once, reuse totals.debit / totals.credit\n```\n\n**`VoucherEditViewModel.isBalanced`** doubles the `Currency.parseRupeeInput` reparsing cost the same way — every SwiftUI read of `canPost` reparses every line's amount string twice. Cache the parsed totals in `@State`/an `@Observable` stored property invalidated only when `lines` changes, rather than as plain computed properties.\n\n**`DashboardViewModel.reload`'s monthly loop** builds a full 4-section P&L per month just to keep `totalExpensesPaise` — same fix as the N+1 item, a single grouped query replaces both the query count and the wasted computation.\n\n---\nSkipped: memory leak category has genuinely only the one finding (checked Timer/NotificationCenter/Combine/weak-self repo-wide) — not padding it with nitpicks. The `VoucherService.loadAccounts` N+1 was already flagged in a prior session and is still unfixed — highest-value place to start since it's on the voucher posting hot path.\n",
